Installation & Local Setup Guide
1. Install Dependencies
pip install fastapi "uvicorn[standard]" ultralytics numpy opencv-python torch pillow \
            python-multipart pymongo "passlib[bcrypt]" "python-jose[cryptography]" \
            pydantic tqdm scikit-learn


(Optional) Create requirements.txt for portability.

2. Ensure MongoDB is Running

Install MongoDB locally or connect to MongoDB Atlas.

Default local connection:

mongodb://localhost:27017


Collections will generate automatically:
users, scans

3.  Set YOLO Model Paths in eliyon_api.py
DOG_EMOTION_PATH = r"C:\...\runs\dog_emotion\weights\best.pt"
CAT_HEALTH_PATH  = r"C:\...\runs\cat_disease\weights\best.pt"
BABY_EAR_MODEL_PATH = r"C:\...\runs\baby_ear_disease\weights\best.pt"


Make sure these .pt files exist.

4. Start FastAPI Backend
uvicorn eliyon_api:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload


Expected output:

Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:8000
Loading Elisyon models for API...
âœ… Models loaded for API.

5.  Open Web App

ğŸ‘‰ Open your browser:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/


ğŸ¯ Features:
âœ¨ Upload or capture photo
âœ¨ Real-time YOLO scanning
âœ¨ Login/signup (JWT authentication)
âœ¨ Scan history dashboard

